snippet.textDisplay:
Because people don't understand this correctly I will correct the Issihn age myth. Spoilers ahead.

The black mortal blade resurrects you at your peak. Issihn was resurrected in the same old body he died in because that body in his last seconds was his peak. This is stated in the "Mushin arts" description that Issihn would never stop learning and so he would never reach an apex of ability. 

What the black mortal blade did do was make Issihn no longer on the verge of death from his disease so he wasn't fighting weakened.
